# Feedbacks that can help speakers

## General feedback
- Introduce yourself in the beginning, which city/community are you from
- Understanding the time duration of the talk can help
- The talk should not be fast to comprehend - speaking slowly could help
- The talk should not be fast to comprehend - giving pauses can help 
- Adding numbers in slides can help audience to quote a question on a page 
- Using light theme (some people find dark background difficult to read)
- Listing and preparing common FAQs asked on your talk

## Things to take care when presenting to remote audience
- Avoid asking question to users from (there might not be a way to get)
- Please prepare demo video, in case demo is not working properly
- Keeping backup wifi ready
